annotation.text:
John's vocal in the introduction single-tracked to create an intimate feel. When Paul's vocals begin with the first verse, John's double-tracked vocals kick in and remain intact for the remainder of the song. They were also careful to make sure Paul's double-tracked vocals were in place for his flub at the end of the second bridge.

The following release has a remaster that has the intro toward the left but all the rest centered:
US: United Artists UAS 6366 Hard Day's Night 1964.
